  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/integration-events/mastering-topic-taxonomies-for-scalable-event-driven-architectures/ev-p/14420004</id>
    <title>Mastering Topic Taxonomies for Scalable Event-Driven Architectures</title>
    <updated>2026-06-16T13:37:28.686000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>ajmaradiaga</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/107</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;A single poorly named topic can break downstream consumers, trigger routing surprises, and make growth painful. These mistakes are common, and they are fixable once a clear taxonomy is in place. This session gives SAP developers, integration architects, and event-driven practitioners a practical, opinionated path to get topic structure right from day one.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Join Solace Developer Advocate Hari Rangarajan and SAP Developer Advocate Antonio Maradiaga for a hands-on webinar focused on topic taxonomy best practices in SAP Advanced Event Mesh. A topic is the structured address that routes an event from producer to consumer. A topic taxonomy is the deliberate, hierarchical naming convention that makes those addresses predictable, governable, and reusable across teams and systems.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;We start with a concise primer that clarifies what topics are in SAP Advanced Event Mesh, why naming decisions shape routing and subscriptions, and how a single off-pattern name can ripple into broken consumers downstream. From there, you will follow a live Event Portal walkthrough inside an application domain that contrasts solid patterns with common anti-patterns. Flat, opaque, or overly generic topic strings lead to real problems: failed event discovery, fan-out explosions, and governance headaches that compound as your system scales. You will see the impact in real time, and you can ask questions as we iterate on designs.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Next, we look at SAP S/4HANA. Its native business events ship with a topic structure that aligns with proven taxonomy principles, which helps teams extend consistently and integrate without reinventing conventions.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;We close with queue naming conventions: clear rules for labeling durable message queues so teams can read, operate, and evolve them confidently across environments. You will see the decision trade-offs and a concrete example in the Event Portal.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;What you will learn:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;How to design a scalable, hierarchical topic taxonomy for SAP Advanced Event Mesh&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;The most common topic anti-patterns, why they happen, and how to avoid them&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;How SAP S/4HANA native events align with best-practice topic structures&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Queue naming conventions: guidelines, decision trade-offs, and a live Event Portal walkthrough&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;How to use the Event Portal application domain view to govern and validate your event landscape&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;Save your seat and bring your use cases for the live Q&amp;amp;A.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/integration-events/mastering-topic-taxonomies-for-scalable-event-driven-architectures/ev-p/14420004"/>
    <published>2026-06-16T13:37:28.686000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
